@barakobama8194 5070 Ti had ~5 in stock at my Microcenter around lunch yesterday for $800 and $900.  The cheaper units sold last night, but the last two didn't sell until after lunch today.  The three 5090s that showed in stock after close last night for $2500 and $2700 sold immediately at opening.

I know the 5070s selling in about 24 hours doesn't sound terrible, but if those were 5080s, they'd be gone in minutes.  I was at the Micro Center in Marietta for vacation when the 5070 Ti launched, and I think the last one (the most expensive, of course) sold the next morning.  People don't appear too keen on 5070 Ti, but wind up going 'well, at least it's a cheaper 4080'.

Still, a cheaper 16GB 4070 Ti i the form of a 9070 XT sounds awesome.  My only complaint is I want a 24GB XTX, but maybe that'll come.  I just hope they were expecting Nvidia to have a real launch and have hundreds per store for this.

